main event: Several slow moving lights were observed in the sky over Omaha, Nebraska, shortly after midnight on July 12, 1968.
interesting points: The lights paused momentarily before shifting direction to the northwest,The officer and several other witnesses interpreted the objects as aircraft rather than UFOs,There were no reports of aircraft being in the vicinity at that time,The objects were observed moving slowly and making no sound,There is no physical evidence left from the incident.
witness description: an officer on duty and several persons who saw the lights
